                            <comment id="433250" author="yujian" created="Tue, 29 Oct 2024 23:51:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Andreas,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;So this might be fixed on master, but failing on b2_15?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yes, I just found it was the b2_15 sanity tests being run because of the client downgrade.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;It might be useful to have something like &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18356&quot; title=&quot;test-framework to fetch except list from server for interop testing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18356&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18356&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; where the server can specify a list of subtests to skip&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yes, this is very useful.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="433248" author="adilger" created="Tue, 29 Oct 2024 23:12:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=yujian&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;yujian&quot;&gt;yujian&lt;/a&gt;, during rolling downgrade this could be running an older client and/or older server?  So this might be fixed on master, but failing on b2_15?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It might be useful to have something like &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18356&quot; title=&quot;test-framework to fetch except list from server for interop testing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18356&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18356&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; where the &lt;b&gt;server&lt;/b&gt; can specify a list of subtests to skip, so that (when it is available in test-framework.sh on the older clients) it is possible to &quot;retroactively skip&quot; specific subtests during interop testing with newer servers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="433083" author="yujian" created="Tue, 29 Oct 2024 00:21:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Still occurred in  rolling-downgrade-client1 test session:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/4c58b377-6fbe-4e69-9ef5-cf1e0e0c5263&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/4c58b377-6fbe-4e69-9ef5-cf1e0e0c5263&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Test session details:&lt;br/&gt;
clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b2_15/94&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b2_15/94&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-553.5.1.el8_10.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
servers: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4588&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4588&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-553.16.1.el8_lustre.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="431926" author="pjones" created="Fri, 18 Oct 2024 22:30:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Merged for 2.16&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="431900" author="gerrit" created="Fri, 18 Oct 2024 18:44:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Oleg Drokin &amp;lt;green@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; merged in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/56643/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/56643/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17047&quot; title=&quot;interop rolling-downgrade-client2 sanity test_77c: no checksum dump file on OSS&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17047&quot;&gt;LU-17047&lt;/a&gt; tests: sanity/77c ensure ost debug_path is valid&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: &lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 0bb0b2938c41c4181d7f536675700606932699f6&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="430845" author="JIRAUSER19283" created="Thu, 10 Oct 2024 04:19:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I proposed a change in &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/56643&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/56643&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
to try to avoid these spurious but frequent test failures.&lt;br/&gt;
While I couldn&apos;t find WHY either get_param is set to &quot;&quot; prior to the test  or if lctl get_param silently fails to read the parameter&lt;br/&gt;
the large number of failed test runs due to this causes pain.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="430815" author="JIRAUSER19283" created="Wed, 9 Oct 2024 23:42:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;All the times this test fails like this it is seems like the filename is corrupted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The filename is supposed to be created using :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
                ost_file_prefix=$(do_facet ost1 $LCTL get_param -n debug_path)
                ost_file_prefix=${ost_file_prefix}-checksum_dump-ost-\\${fid}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which suggests that the ...get_param... occasionally returns &quot;&quot; instead of the expected &quot;/tmp/lustre-log&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
so we end up with a filename &quot;-checksum-dump...&quot; which does not exist.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;60f does run prior to this and modifies debug_path so that could affect 77c if it fails to restore debug_path correctly. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="430186" author="yujian" created="Fri, 4 Oct 2024 07:04:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The same failure occurred in b2_15&amp;lt;-&amp;gt;master rolling-downgrade-mds-zfs test session:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/972c05c9-edb8-4120-a134-90423f06132e&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/972c05c9-edb8-4120-a134-90423f06132e&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="383348" author="adilger" created="Tue, 22 Aug 2023 23:38:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10019&quot; title=&quot;Interop - sanity test_77c: no checksum dump file on OSS&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10019&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10019&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, except that ticket related to interop between versions that did not support the &quot;checksum_dump&quot; feature.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this case, both the old and new versions &lt;b&gt;should&lt;/b&gt; support &quot;checksum_dump&quot; so it isn&apos;t clear why it isn&apos;t working.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
